cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper focuses on the use of deep learning in computer vision, specifically in image segmentation, classification, and detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The use of neural networks also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), and the comparison of different network architectures could fit under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of facial databases suggests it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and the use of art images could suggest cs.MM (Multimedia).
